title: Tiger and Charlie Woods shoot 15-under 57 | Round 2 | PNC Championship | 2024
description:
In the final round of the 2024 PNC Championship, Tiger and Charlie Woods card a 15-under 57 to finish runner-up to Bernhard and Jason Langer at 28-under par.

SUBSCRIBE to PGA TOUR now: http://pgat.us/vBxcZSh

‚Ä¢ The PGA TOUR heads to Florida this week for the PNC Championship as 19 impressive family duos challenge over two days for the title. Tiger and Charlie Woods return for the fifth time as a pair and look for their first win at this event. Tiger‚Äôs start this week comes after he underwent his sixth back surgery in September to alleviate back spasms and pain he had been experiencing throughout 2024. The pair finished tied for fifth last year with their best being solo second in 2021. John Daly and his son John Daly II will also be in the field this week. They claimed 2nd place in 2022, T5 last year and were victorious in 2021. John Daly‚Äôs highest finish this year was T22 at the American Family Insurance Championship in September. Bernard Langer and son Jason will look to successfully defend their title from a year ago. The win in 2023 was Langer's fifth PNC Championship victory, tying the all-time record. He's won three times with Jason and twice with his older son, Stefan. Others to look out for are Vijay Singh and his son Qass, Matt Kuchar and his son Carson, and Nelly Korda and her father Petr.

title: Charlie Woods makes first-ever HOLE-IN-ONE at PNC Championship | 2024
description:
In the final round of the 2024 PNC Championship, Charlie Woods cards his first-ever ace in TOUR-sanctioned competition on the 176-yard, par-3 4th hole at Ritz-Carlton GC. 

SUBSCRIBE to PGA TOUR now: http://pgat.us/vBxcZSh

The PGA TOUR heads to Florida this week for the PNC Championship as 19 impressive family duos challenge over two days for the title. Tiger and Charlie Woods return for the fifth time as a pair and look for their first win at this event. Tiger‚Äôs start this week comes after he underwent his sixth back surgery in September to alleviate back spasms and pain he had been experiencing throughout 2024. The pair finished tied for fifth last year with their best being solo second in 2021. John Daly and his son John Daly II will also be in the field this week. They claimed 2nd place in 2022, T5 last year and were victorious in 2021. John Daly‚Äôs highest finish this year was T22 at the American Family Insurance Championship in September. Bernard Langer and son Jason will look to successfully defend their title from a year ago. The win in 2023 was Langer's fifth PNC Championship victory, tying the all-time record. He's won three times with Jason and twice with his older son, Stefan. Others to look out for are Vijay Singh and his son Qass, Matt Kuchar and his son Carson, and Nelly Korda and her father Petr.

title: Sabrina Carpenter: Tiny Desk Concert
description:
Ashley Pointer | December 20, 2024
When I greeted Sabrina Carpenter at NPR HQ for her Tiny Desk debut, her charm was immediately disarming. Bubbling with excitement, she extended her hand, introduced herself and complimented my outfit with genuine warmth. You‚Äôd think this was one of her first ‚Äúbig time‚Äù gigs, not a regular performance for a pop veteran, having sold out arenas across the country touring her now six time Grammy-nominated sixth album, Short n‚Äô Sweet. That humility made me love her even more. 

But Carpenter delivers far more than just charm in this performance. Backed by her band, complimented with pedal steel and a string quartet, she reimagines her biggest hits from Short n‚Äô Sweet, while sharing the stories in between songs of how these tracks came to life. Opening with ‚ÄúTaste,‚Äù strings serve up some playful pizzicato, before Carpenter and her band move into a lush, soulful version ‚ÄúBed Chem.‚Äù Then everyone swaps their electric instruments for acoustic to perform ‚ÄúPlease Please Please‚Äù and ‚ÄúSlim Pickins.‚Äù Finally, Carpenter closes with the viral favorite ‚ÄúJuno,‚Äù cheekily asking the audience, ‚ÄúHave you ever tried this one?‚Äù before sweeping her rear end across the windchimes, earning a laugh from the room. 

‚ÄúWhen I first started [writing songs] it was kinda in a room like this ‚Äî a room with very dry walls and there‚Äôs no reverb,‚Äù Carpenter reflects at the top of her performance. ‚ÄúBut there‚Äôs something so real and special.‚Äù That authenticity set the tone for a memorable session with one of 2024‚Äôs biggest breakout superstars.

title: Tiger and Charlie Woods shoot 13-under 59 | Round 1 | PNC Championship | 2024
description:
In the opening round of the 2024 PNC Championship, Tiger and Charlie Woods shoot a 13-under 59 to share the lead with defending champions Team Langer and past champions Team Singh.
 
SUBSCRIBE to PGA TOUR now: http://pgat.us/vBxcZSh

‚Ä¢ The PGA TOUR heads to Florida this week for the PNC Championship as 19 impressive family duos challenge over two days for the title. Tiger and Charlie Woods return for the fifth time as a pair and look for their first win at this event. Tiger‚Äôs start this week comes after he underwent his sixth back surgery in September to alleviate back spasms and pain he had been experiencing throughout 2024. The pair finished tied for fifth last year with their best being solo second in 2021. John Daly and his son John Daly II will also be in the field this week. They claimed 2nd place in 2022, T5 last year and were victorious in 2021. John Daly‚Äôs highest finish this year was T22 at the American Family Insurance Championship in September. Bernard Langer and son Jason will look to successfully defend their title from a year ago. The win in 2023 was Langer's fifth PNC Championship victory, tying the all-time record. Ok so The Superman Trailer is now here and it's packed with easter eggs, big characters and a lot of things to talk about. Throughout this video we're gonna be breaking down the teaser and talking about everything you might have missed. Welcome to the Heavy Spoilers show, I'm your host Paul and this is a trailer I've been waiting for for a long long time. James Gunns DCU is slowly ramping up and this is a great first look at whats to come. So with that out the way, thank you for clicking this, now let's get into the Superman Trailer.

-

Ok so the trailer opens with Superman crashing into some snowy terrain. This feels like it riffs slightly off the moment in Man Of Steel where Clark crashes during his first flight. That was after he just came out of the fortress of Solitude or rather the ship from Krypton that was pretty much the DCEU version of that. I do feel like this landscapes a similar sort of thing with the fortress likely being around here. The teaser to the teaser showed an image of a metallic door with the house of EL symbol upon it. This was likely the Fortress's door and I feel like he could be returning here.

We see the crystals forming at one point which emphasise what the world was like. This is something the Reeves film had and its a crystal type planet thats likely just like this. It also makes it feel otherworldly and I cant wait to see how it appears in the movie.¬†

Now as for the fortress itself, typically in the comics it was normally shown as having a giant keyhole at the entrance. Superman then opened it using a key that was made from the planets densest metal. This would be impossible for anyone else to lift and thus it was...was pretty secure. More men tried to get into it than Lily Phillips but it kept things locked down.

Call of Duty: Black Ops 6 is a 2024 first-person shooter video game co-developed by Treyarch and Raven Software and published by Activision. It is the twenty-first installment of the Call of Duty series and is the seventh main entry in the Black Ops sub-series, following Call of Duty: Black Ops Cold War (2020). Set during Operation Desert Storm, Black Ops 6's single-player story follows rogue CIA operatives Troy Marshall and Frank Woods as they assemble a team of agents to hunt down Pantheon, a paramilitary group with covert ties to the agency.

Call of Duty: Warzone[a] was a 2020 free-to-play battle royale first-person shooter game developed by Raven Software and Infinity Ward and published by Activision. It was released on March 10, 2020, for PlayStation 4, Windows, and Xbox One as part of Call of Duty: Modern Warfare (2019) and was subsequently connected to Call of Duty: Black Ops Cold War (2020) and Call of Duty: Vanguard (2021), but did not require purchase of any of the aforementioned titles.[2] Warzone allowed online multiplayer combat among 150 players and featured both cross-platform play and cross-platform progression between the three aforementioned titles.

title: The AMOC Might Be WAY More Unstable Than We Thought...Here's Why
description:
Take the PBS Digital Studios Audience Survey: https://to.pbs.org/2024SurveyWTHR 

There is a mysterious cold blob in the North Atlantic that could be a warning sign that the largest heat transfer system on the planet, the AMOC, is on the brink of collapse. But it turns out that the AMOC‚Äôs collapse is a highly debated topic among scientists ‚Äì climate models are inconsistent and there isn‚Äôt enough observational data to determine a trend. So, perhaps the answer to understand a possible AMOC collapse is to go back in time. 

In this episode, we talk to three paleoclimate experts who look at the Earth‚Äôs past climate and find some really shocking things about the AMOC‚Äôs past behavior. And it turns out that the mysterious cold blob may actually be a bigger deal than we realize‚Ä¶ 

Weathered is a show hosted by weather expert Maiya May and produced by Balance Media that helps explain the most common natural disasters, what causes them, how they‚Äôre changing, and what we can do to prepare.
